caption: Food was good service was fast. Nice atmosphere and art.

The food is amazing, good quality and consistent in taste. The staff are very welcoming and they love explaining the difference between the different dishes. We have tried most of the items on the menu and nothing has disappointed us. We personally love the seafood volcano, fisherman’s madness, and the red curry. The ingredients, chicken and seafood are all top quality and you can feel it when you have the food (no MSG). You can also ask them to spice it up to your liking. We have had the food close to 10 times and it has been top notch every single time. Undoubtedly the best Thai food we have had out of the 20+ Thai restaurants we have tried in the New England area.

This was such an awesome find. I have been searching for some good Thai food since I moved to Boston and now I’ve found it! I own a few Thai restaurants myself back in Denver and this definitely reminded me so much of my own food. The Thai ice tea is killer! Overall such a wonderful experience will become a regular!
Very average. Everything tastes like fish sauce.
My fav thai place ever! Love love love the padthai and mi katang !!! Everyone should give these 2 dishes a try. So worth it!
Food was exceptionally good but their service tops it all!
I regularly come grabbing some food in this place. I enjoyed the efficient service and well prepared dishes. Highly recommended.

I tried the brown sugar mango fried rice. It was good, but not as special as I had expected. It tastes more like the regular pineapple fried rice. The seafood dish my friend had is a better choice. The server was really nice, too.
Very comfortable environment and decent Thai food. The Drunken Noodle portions were good and I enjoyed my meal here.

I meet with friends this lovely place quite a bit! This is my favorite restaurant to dine.  I visit this spot at least once a month. The meals are of high quality, the crew is helpful and the rates are reasonable. I like meeting in this place over a good meal.
Staff made me feel confortable with their cleaning and sanitizing procedures. Service and food are delicious. Will come back again

One of my fav locations for tasty Thai food. i should have took a photo of the food but it was too good to interrupt. quick and friendly service. feels like a place in charlotte that i enjoyed visiting.

This is the best Thai restaurant in the Greater Boston area!!! Excellent, tasty, authentic food that is fresh and outstandingly delicious. Drunken noodle is my favorite and the Fresh Rolls are so good. The fried ice cream just might be the best dessert you'll ever have! Trust me on this...try it! Also, the owners are so very kind and friendly....it feels good to support such good people. Dine-in now or delivery....either way....The Similans is a MUST TRY!!!

I adore this restaurant! They have delicious meals, their menu is nice, The chief cook in that restaurant is well trained, I like a lot tasting all their dishes. The dishes are always tasty, the attitude towards the guests  is very good too. I visit often this restaurant and I not even once was unsatisfied.  I highly recommend it.
I would say this place is overrated, had better Thai food at other places.
Great padthai
Best thai place in the area, good ambience!
quick service. consistent flavors that are top notch quality.
Subpar service and mediocre food, but prices are decent so ok for a cheap dinner before going out to something else. Likely even better if consumed on the way back from a night on the town.

My fav Thai restaurant in the city! Have been going there for 4+ years. I've tried random choices on their (super long) menu and had some great surprises and some fine experiences. Overall, highly recommend this place, especially their traditional foods like classic pad Thai.
Good pad thai

I came here for lunch on a Friday, and it was pretty much full. I had to wait a bit for a seat, and service was quite slow. I intended to come here for a quick lunch, but that didn't work out. Anyway, I got an order of green onion pancake and tom yum noodle soup with flat rice noodles. The green onion pancake wasn't good and wasn't flavorful, I would not recommend it. It was too doughy. The tom yum noodle soup was very flavorful and I really enjoyed it. The noodles were really chewy, and I liked the amount of seafood and meat in it, although there was too much meat. The chicken was quite dry and there was a lot of pork. I also ordered a spicy pad kee mao, red curry, and green curry to go. The pad kee mao noodles were lacking flavor, but both the red and green curries were delicious. They didn't pack it to-go initially though, so the rice in the curries was soggy with sauce. I wasn't very happy about that, but the flavors and tofu were really delicious. The food is quite cheap for Thai food, and it was great. I would recommend this place if you're not in a rush!
Excellent food and great service.
Huge portions of delicious, spicy food

Got the brown sugar mango chicken curry (a house special) and it was delicious! Great flavours, loved the mix of mango and heat. I wish it was spicier (and I think the next time I go, I will ask them to make it spicier).
Great food Good service; a small hiccup but quickly fixed! Perfect  Will be back for sure
Amazing food! I didn't expect the larb dishes to be this good or authentic when I ordered. Glad I found this place (through ubereats).
One of my favorite Thai restaurants. The food is some of the best Thai I've had.
Super! Food & staff just lovely. I'm going to go back.

A comfortable environment for the customers. This restaurant is very well decorated. I am very happy with the experience I got from this restaurant. Foods taste so delicious and spicy. Special foods include Thai Spring Rolls, Tom Yum Goong, Brown Sugar Duck.
Favorite Thai place
Very tasty fresh good, great service!
Was not impressed with the Tom Yum Soup. They either overcooked the chicken or used ones but it tasted terrible
There food is amazing. I went there yesterday and I'm already in love. If they need something theyl  give it to you in the snap of a finger. Great just great
The best Thai food I've had in Boston - tastes exactly like how the food was when I was in Chiang Mai, especially the "country style Pad Thai!"
Good pad thai.
The food was way too salty.
Great food. Wonderful locale
Great Thai place. I would highly recommend. They get very crowded at lunch time :-) Good sign.
Good food
Great food

I thought the food was quite disappointing. the Tom Yum soup (a staple Thai dish that's hard to get wrong) lacked flavor! It was actually bland, no lemongrass or that great sour flavor. Kaprow, another basic Thai staple, lacked the same.  Maybe this is an ok restaurant for people new to Thai food, but definitely lacking in authenticity and flavor. Never had bland Thai food like that before.
Best Thai food I’ve ever had
The food was amazing! Thank you for the Catering! Can recommend this place!!!
Great, fast service! Good food!
Great customer service!
Lovely dining room, small bar, nice background music. Excellent Thai food. Have sent a lot of people there and they all loved it and continue to go back.

I'd say the food is as expected from a Thai restaurant, and the venue is large and has a nice atmosphere. I liked the atmosphere, and portion size was typical for food. I got the tofu drunken noodle, and the staff was nice about not having fish sauce in the dishes which is something I worry about at Thai places.
Great
Nice place. Can get crowded. If you're vegetarian, there will always be a fishy flavor to the food (even if they insist it isn't).
Beef noodle soup is my favorite. Veru reasonable prices
Nice restaurant ambiance and good food.

Neat place, good decor, courteous staff, quick service, lot of options-even for vegetarians. We tried drunken noodles, fisherman madness, country style pad Thai (veg). All of these were delicious. Look forward to many more visits and trying out other items.

Staff is great and food is even better. The price is pretty decent for a fancy place like this restaurant, the atmosphere is amazing feels like an actual Thai place with good taste in decoration. Definitely not a cheap looking in and out takeout place, you can dine in style here!!! Try the seafood volcano you’ll love it!! Also I made the mistake of going 3 peppers hot. There’s a reason they keep it to 2 peppers. My spicy food loving friends be careful

This place was pretty good! We got the duck chili and the gra pow. Both were appropriately spicy and delicious!
Very good This food, nice decor, a bit romantic and excellent service.  Good for an intimate near of family get together.  Parking can be a bit of a challenge.
This may be the best Thai food in America. I'm not kidding. People I know who have been to Thailand swear this is actually much better than the real thing.
Great Thai food right behind the Galleria mall.
Don’t know much about Thai food, but this tasted AMAZING. Friendly service, comfortable atmosphere, fair prices. Will definitely return!!
One of the best Thai places in town. Plan for a 10-15 minute wait during lunch time. The service is fast however the quality of food is top notch.
Great service, promptly served, food was great.
Food was amazing . Pad thai is amazing. Papaya salad was delicious. I loved the pad si ou.
Very good Thai cuisine but parking can be a bit challenging.  Worth the short walk
One of my all time fav Thai joint. Food is consistent and staff are nice and attentive. Sue (hope i got her name right) is always fun to chat with. Decor is pretty nice too.
One of the best pho in the city! Great customer service also. Been coming here for years, never failed me! Lunch specials are a great deal.

Very nice restaurant and excellent Thai Food. Great Location at the heart of East Cambridge. We had a very delicious meal. However the waitresses were pushy. That's the only issues. The bathroom doesn't have a clear gender sign. So it was quite confusing.

Great thai place with variety of food. Highly recommended.
Great food and attentive service. Nicely decorated with Southeast Asian artifacts.
The panang curry chicken is excellent.  Close walk from Cambridge South mall.

Classic pad Thai and red curry dish with duck all had super fresh vegetables and were perfectly seasoned.  Great for an intimate date or a family night out.  Comfortable, quiet atmosphere and spacious enough.  Food was fairly priced, appropriately portioned and lovely.  Kids enjoyed the salt water fish tanks on display.  Went here while in town based on reviews and it did not disappoint.  We'll be back!
Good cheap Thai food. Can't go wrong stopping by for lunch!
Not just the best Thai choice in Kendall Sq But one of the best in Boston.
So good, and the traditional menu choices were matched with excellent preparation!
Really liked the rice with chicken and shrimps highly recommended

Very fresh tasting Thai lunch in a spacious restaurant with ok service. Check if you plate has been properly washed.
Ordered a basil fried rice here and wasn't disappointed. It is very busy at most of the times.
One of my favorite local Thai restaurants!
Awesome!  Reasonable prices, great food, good portions couldn't eat it all.

Not the best Thai food but over all was good. Satay was a bit dry and tom kha gai soup was a bit sweet.
It’s good food considering how pricey cambridge is, I like the shrimp bok choy, fried rice, and beef teriyaki, those are my go tos for lunch

Great thai food in the Kendall area. Large portions, so great value for the price. Got the roasted duck curry, which was perfectly spicy to pair with a bowl of rice. I would also recommend the pad Thai. The thai iced tea was a little too sweet for my taste buds. Overall great experience.

We went with a group of 22 and they were very quick to accommodate us as we only called up like an hour earlier. The waitress was a little grumpy seeing the group even though they took 20% gratuity. The drinks were deprived of alcohol and 2 maitai didn't even give a buzz.  Appetizers were tasty, main courses hit and miss. Shrimp Scampi was ok, duck chilli was tasty.

The food is really good and is very busy over lunch.   They work very hard to minimize the wait.   However,  in our group an order got lost and when we asked to split the check the didn't do it right there first time.
Whenever we're in Cambridge, this is our go to place.  Prices are reasonable and the food is fantastic.  We have never been disappointed!!

Food - Tasted good. The menu is not vegetarian friendly (very less pure vegetarian options).  Ambience - Good ambience.  Service - Great service. All the waiters were warm and welcoming and made sure we were comfortable and got what we needed.

More upscale casual joint for a quick bite or formal sitdown dinner. Real linen napkins and nice table setting. Great noodle soups and I would recommend the duck noodle soup. Nice hearty flavorful broth and plentiful slices of duck.
Decent food but too expensive for what you get.

The food is awesome. I have been here for more than 10 times. I love the food. I am disappointed in service most of the time. Waitresses are always in a rush. They literally behave rude. We asked for 5 minutes to decide and she came 5-6 times between that. We gave enough tip still they were not satisfied and trying to take bill receipt very rudely. You can not ask customer for more tip. Its depend on your service. Arrogant staff. I recommend you guys for food!!
Delicious. Scallion pancakes are the best
Delicious food and great value for money.
I ordered Tom Yam Kung, spicy and nice. I would like to try different dishes.

The Tom Ka Gai was served in a bowl so small it was hard for a baby corn not to stick out of the bowl. Their Thai iced tea was great. Service was very good.
Delicious Thai food, quick service and reasonable price

I heard very positive feedback about this place so I ordered the green chicken curry, beef drunk noodles, spring rolls (I think it was pork or something) and chicken satay. 15 Minutes after eating dinner I started throwing up and I still am on the next day. I would never order or go to this restaurant again.
Great Thai food, reasonable prices and friendly service. Perfect location to grab lunch out from the office. Highly recommended!
Pricey and my food was just ok. I've had better for less money but I wouldn't say I'm never going back.
Nice food for vegetarians too

Decent Thai food, quick service. The lady operating the register can be a bit short/nippy, especially when it's really busy. Nice atmosphere and great tasting Thai food.
There is one word that describes this restaurant. Consistent. You will always get good food, good service and easy on the pocket.

Decent thai food,  great for lunch portion size and speed!
Best green curry I had in my life.

Little expensive than the other thai places around but wide variety of food with plenty of options for vegans.

Very good Thai. I always like the Drunken Noodle or Chicken Gaprow. Excellent Thai Iced Tea, too.

I want to set this review up with some pertinent information. I’ve been in the food biz for 30 years and don’t take reviews lightly. We ordered take out last night because we have a new puppy and couldn’t afford the time to sit and enjoy dinner out. I’ll say the food was excellent. Here’s the caveat. We asked for extra duck sauce because we ordered two rice dishes and two other duck dishes. We like duck sauce with the rice dishes. We were told it doesn’t come with any of these dishes and would have to pay for it. Really? The cost is $1 per container. Even spending $70 didn’t shift their consideration to throw a couple containers in. Upon opening the bag at home we saw one container which had exactly 1 ounce of sauce. Really? Yes one ounce. I was mortified. Just poor business acumen at work here. They should rethink their approach to making money.
Enormous menu with all the standard Thai dishes and plenty of unique and interesting dishes. Everything I've had here has been great.

This place was average. It was easy to find a table on a Friday night. Service was okay, nothing especially great or bad about it. You get a lot of food for the price, but it was pretty bland. The khao soi at Cha Yen in Watertown is 10,000 times better. I recommend anyone wanting really good Thai food go there before ever going here. Really, if you're nearby and want a decent dinner that will give you leftovers for the next day, this place will be fine, but the food was only okay. Also, the corner where we were sitting smelled like a bathroom, which was very off putting. Also off putting but slightly more amusing is the anatomically detailed statue of elephants mating up on a shelf in the back left corner of the restaurant.
Very depends on your seat
Typical Americanized Thai restaurant.

Service could be improved. We were served food at different times, and the younger staff are nice, but I didn't appreciate how the older one simply dismissed our request of separate bills. The other staff accommodated us. The food was okay but not  delicious.

Good Thai food. We had the pad see ew and a curry. The curry was disappointing because it did not come in a bowl, it came on a regular plate, so there actually wasn't all that much curry. The pad see ew was really good though, would definitely come back, but wouldn't get the curry again.

I regularly go to Similans for lunch. The food tastes amazing and seems pretty authentic. I especially like the "Tom Khai Gar" (chicken coconut soup) and the "Thai Friedrice". The service is decent, spice level good, and price affordable. Mind you, it's a little difficult to find a place during lunch as they are so popular and there's usually a wait. But it's worth it!
One of my favorite Thai restaurants in the Boston area. Tasty food, great decor, and friendly staff.
The food seemed ok but not great It's not certified thai food
Good food. Decent price.
Food was amazing!!
Food is very good. Not great for vegetarian or gluten free.

Friendly staff, flavorful food, and reasonable prices. Looking in through the window at night wouldn't give you a very good first impression, though, as there were plenty of empty tables when I brought my family there.
High quality Thai food at better than average priced. Wholeheartedly recommend.

Sumptuous flavors, very detailed menu, and nice atmosphere and service. Great varied veggies in all the dishes. Recommend.

I get food from here literally every week! Nice diversity of dishes and if you ask for your food "very very spicy" they will happily oblige (for me personally I find it challenging to get food spicy enough from many of the other local Thai places).
Great Thai place in East Cambridge. The Masaman Curry was delicious and can't go wrong with it. Just wish they gave me more.
Great food as always. Love it. The ambience can feel a little weird though at first look
